                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12076ZawaldaMaryam">Zawalda
                           Māryām</persName> is mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#104va">104va</locus>.<date>Hand a and c: first half of the18th century; Hand b:
                           17th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይብል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>አ፡</abbr> for <expan>አሜን፡ </expan> (<locus from="94vb" to="104rb">94vb-104rb</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of Texts I-III; directives to
                           the ministers and their abbreviations; titles of books to be read;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; halle luya “Hallelujah”, ʾǝsma
                           la-ʿālam “since for eternity”, sǝmʿanni “listen” in Text III (fols.
                           3ra-7ra); ʾǝgäle in Text III, ʾamen “Amen” and its abbreviation in Text
                           III (fols. 94vb-104rb); elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 On the
                           incipit page of Text III (fols. 36vb), two lines are rubricated
                           (alternating with a black line).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
